ENTRY            F0630   20251216   20260305   20260305       F105
SUBENT        F0630001   20251216   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                  9         13
TITLE      Investigation of backward alpha-particle scattering in
           24Mg and 28Si through alpha-gamma angular correlations
AUTHOR     (R.Prasad,A.Hofmann,F.Vogler)
INSTITUTE  (2GERUEN)
REFERENCE  (J,NP/A,255,64,1975)
FACILITY   (VDGT,2GERUEN)
DETECTOR   (GELI) For detection of the gamma-rays a detector
           having an active volume of 40 cm3 was used. It was
           placed at 90 degr. in the reaction plane.
METHOD     (GSPEC)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-S) Statistical error
HISTORY    (20030827C)
           (20251216U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              13
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           16
SUBENT        F0630002   20251216   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                  6         13
REACTION   (12-MG-24(A,INL)12-MG-24,PAR,DA/DA,G/A,AV)
ANG-SEC    (ANG,A)
           (ANG1,G)
DETECTOR   (SIBAR) Diameter is 4 mm, was used to detect the alpha-
           particles scattered at a mean angle of 178 degr.
           (SOLST) Six detectors spaced at 10 degr. intervals were
           movable over a range 115 to 170 degr. with respect to
           the incident beam axis.
SAMPLE     (12-MG-24,ENR=0.9984) Self-supporting 24Mg target was
           0.5 mg/cm2 in thickness and isotropically enriched to
           99.84% purity.
STATUS     (CURVE,,R.Prasad+,J,NP/A,255,64,1975) Figs 3-5
HISTORY    (20251216U) SD: BIB updated. ANG2-CM -> ANG-CM.
ENDBIB              13
COMMON               5          3
ANG1       EN-MIN     EN-MAX     ANG-ERR-D  ERR-DIG
ADEG       MEV        MEV        ADEG       PER-CENT
        90.       15.5       17.0        0.5        0.1
ENDCOMMON            3
